Advertising expenditure in  Kenya 
jumped 56 percent in the first quarter to 12 billion shillings
($144 million), Business Daily reported, citing Synovate, a
market-research company.   Expenditure grew from 7.7 billion shillings a year earlier
on improved confidence among companies that they will grow their
revenue from increased consumption, the Nairobi-based newspaper
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
